<item>
            <title>[JDK-8304031] Classfile API cannot encode Primitive Class as Condy</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8304031</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Consider this code example:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;cob.constantInstruction(clazz.describeConstable().orElseThrow());&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This fails for primitive classes, as Classfile API always assume ClassDescs are always encodeable as a class constant. The check in BytecodeHelpers should check for&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;if (constantValue instanceof ClassDesc value &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !value.isPrimitive())&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
As only classes or interfaces or arrays are eligible to be encoded in class constants. Discovered while converting SerialPersistentFieldsTest for &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8294977&quot; title=&quot;Convert test/jdk/java tests from ASM library to Classfile API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8294977&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8294977&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.</description>
